    "summary": "I'm a sociologist of science, with my main research focused on on the production and dissemination of scientific knowledge, particularly in physics, science and intercultural communication, and studies on expertise. I am currently part of the Global Epistemologies and Ontologies (GEOS) project at Wageningen University (WUR), where I do research on the role of scientists and experts in Mexican and Brazilian policymaking settings. I am also a part-time lecturer for the WUR Philosophy Department on courses devoted to scientific ethics, philosophy of science and Social Studies of Science. Finally, I am an Associate Editor for the journal Tapuya: Latin American Science, Technology and Society, where aparte from back-office editorial and translation work, I focus on infrastructural open access publishing issues.",
