                    "company": "Cardiff University / Prifysgol Caerdydd",
                    "description": "British Academy Post-Doctoral Fellow with research focusing on Open Access publication policies. The project starts out by analysing the arXiv pre-print server in physics as a highly successful case of 'green' Open Access' implementation. Through interviews with arXiv founders and current staff, it will look at different dimensions of OA implementation problematics and how arXiv has 'solved' issues such as: content filtration and standardisation, reclassification of submissions, embedding of the existing physics social structures into arXiv's organisation. In conjunction with another ongoing ESRC research project also co-written by me, we will also trace differences between the social structures of physics publishing and dissemination and boundaries. Apart from its main focus on physics, the project will also propose that Open Access policies at all levels must be aware of the differences between different knowledge traditions that require different approaches to knowledge dissemination (viz. the specificities of knowledge dissemination practices in other fields of natural science, the humanities and social sciences that make up their localised social dynamics).",
                    "title": "Research Associate",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
